\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.\
In a heavy skillet, add the oil and heat over medium-high heat. Add the onion, carrot, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/celery/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 celery}}, and garlic. Cook, stirring often until vegetables are soft, about 8 minutes. Set aside until cool enough to handle.\
In a large bowl combine the sauteed vegetables, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/ground-beef/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 ground beef}}, chorizo, and diced {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/poblano-chile/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 poblano chile}}.\
In a medium bowl, combine the salt, pepper, cayenne, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cumin/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cumin}}, and eggs. Add the ketchup and sour cream. Mix well with a fork and pour it on top of the mixed meats. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and mix thoroughly with clean hands.\
\
Put the mixture into a 9 by 13-inch loaf-pan. Bake until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/meatloaf/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 meatloaf}} registers 160 degrees F, about 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from the oven and carefully pour off any accumulated pan juices.\
Meanwhile, heat a heavy skillet over high heat. Add the whole {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tomato/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 tomatoes}}, onion, garlic cloves, and serrano chiles. Cook, turning frequently, until lightly charred on all sides. Peel the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garlic}} cloves. Add all the charred ingredients to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/blender/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 blender}}. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pulse/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Pulse}} until chunky, then pour into a small skillet. Stir in the sugar, chipotle chile and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mustard/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mustard}}. Bring the mixture to a boil over medium heat. Cook until slightly thickened, about 4 to 5 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.\
Slice the meatloaf and arrange on a platter. Spoon the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salsa/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 salsa}}-glaze over the meatloaf and serve.}